\cf3 \strokec3 26 
\f1\b0 In the sixth month of Elizabeth\'92s pregnancy, God sent the angel Gabriel to Nazareth, a town in Galilee, 
\f0\b 27 
\f1\b0 to a virgin pledged to be married to a man named Joseph, a descendant of David. The virgin\'92s name was Mary. 
\f0\b 28 
\f1\b0 The angel went to her and said, \'93Greetings, you who are highly favored! The Lord is with you.\'94\cf2 \strokec2 \

\f0\b \cf3 \strokec3 29 
\f1\b0 Mary was greatly troubled at his words and wondered what kind of greeting this might be. 
\f0\b 30 
\f1\b0 But the angel said to her, \'93Do not be afraid, Mary; you have found favor with God. 
\f0\b 31 
\f1\b0 You will conceive and give birth to a son, and you are to call him Jesus. 
\f0\b 32 
\f1\b0 He will be great and will be called the Son of the Most High. The Lord God will give him the throne of his father David, 
\f0\b 33 
\f1\b0 and he will reign over Jacob\'92s descendants forever; his kingdom will never end.\'94\cf2 \strokec2 \

\f0\b \cf3 \strokec3 34 
\f1\b0 \'93How will this be,\'94 Mary asked the angel, \'93since I am a virgin?\'94\cf2 \strokec2 \

\f0\b \cf3 \strokec3 35 
\f1\b0 The angel answered, \'93The Holy Spirit will come on you, and the power of the Most High will overshadow you. So the holy one to be born will be called\'a0the Son of God. 
\f0\b 36 
\f1\b0 Even Elizabeth your relative is going to have a child in her old age, and she who was said to be unable to conceive is in her sixth month. 
\f0\b 37 
\f1\b0 For no word from God will ever fail.\'94\cf2 \strokec2 \

\f0\b \cf3 \strokec3 38 
\f1\b0 \'93I am the Lord\'92s servant,\'94 Mary answered. \'93May your word to me be fulfilled.\'94 Then the angel left her.\cf2 \strokec2 \

\f0\b \cf3 \strokec3 39 
\f1\b0 At that time Mary got ready and hurried to a town in the hill country of Judea, 
\f0\b 40 
\f1\b0 where she entered Zechariah\'92s home and greeted Elizabeth.\cf2 \strokec2  \
